            "@type": "IrrigationRequirement",
            "quantity": "After planting, sprinkler, splashing or pot irrigation is helpful for sprouting. After the first earthing, subsequent irrigations can be done in the furrows. Light irrigation may be required at an interval of 5 to 10 days depending on the nature of the soil and weather condition. In no case the plants should be allowed to wilt. Over irrigation should be avoided. The safe limit is to allow irrigation water in the furrows to the extent of 2/3rd of the height of the ridges.",
